# shellcheck shell=bash
# shellcheck disable=SC1090,SC1091,SC2034,SC2148,SC2154,SC2155,SC2296,SC2299,SC2317

# This file contains ZSH-specific configurations that may not be fully compatible
# with shellcheck's Bash analysis. The following disables are explained:
#
# SC1090: Can't follow non-constant source (dynamic sourcing like nvm, zoxide)
# SC1091: Not following sourced file (oh-my-zsh, completion scripts)
# SC2034: Variable appears unused (ZSH-specific variables and theme settings)
# SC2148: Shebang not found (this is sourced, not executable)
# SC2154: Variable is referenced but not assigned (ZSH provides these)
# SC2155: Declare and assign separately (common in exports)
# SC2296: Parameter expansion can't be parsed (ZSH-specific syntax)
# SC2299: Array expansion may be unsupported (ZSH array syntax)
# SC2317: Command appears to be unreachable (hook functions)

# Add these directives to the top of .zshrc or create .shellcheckrc in your home directory
# To run shellcheck on .zshrc: shellcheck -x ~/.zshrc

# Recommended shellcheck command for .zshrc:
# shellcheck -x --enable=all --severity=style ~/.zshrc